fbc6766d-9b85-42f6-b633-da07a0b47941.59fd0cd9-4ae0-4dac-a4be-a09ec8c8e86b.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

fbc6766d-9b85-42f6-b633-da07a0b47941.description=
Synopsis

    This flow retrieves the LIF info based on the vServer.
    getLifInfoByVserver performs the following steps\:
      1. Check that the vServer exists.
      2. Retrieve the LIF and Interface information.
      3. Iterate through and compile an xslt list of LIFs.
      4. Set the LIF variables (name, address, netmask, and netmask length).
      5. Check for a LIF address.
      6. If at least one LIF address exists, create and IPHostAddress based on the address.
      7. Iterate through the LIF list and compile a list of net interface protocols based on the LIF (or LIFs).

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer to be used in the flow.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case the LIF info for a particular vServer. See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".


Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
